{"title_page": "LaSalle College", "text_new": "{{distinguish|text=[[La Salle College]], Hong Kong}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2007}}\n{{advert|date=March 2013}}\n}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name         = LaSalle College/Montreal\n|image_name   = New LaSalle-Montreal H En.png\n|image_size   = \n|motto        = Make it happen\n|established  = 1959\n|type         = [[College education in Quebec|College]]\n|affiliation = Non-Denominational\n|endowment    = \n|chancellor   = \n|president    =  \n|city         = [[Montreal]]\n|state        = [[Quebec]]\n|country      = [[Canada]]\n| coor        = {{Coord|45|29|29|N|73|34|53|W|display=inline,title|type:edu}}\n|students = International & Local\n|undergrad    =  Pre-university, Technical\n|postgrad     =  Not available\n|faculty      = \n|staff        = \n|alumni       =  \n|campus       = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n|free_label   = Sports teams\n|free         = \n|colours      = [[Blue (color)|Blue]] {{color box|#072B61}} & Orange\n|nickname = \n|address= 2000 Sainte-Catherine Street West<br/>H3H 2T2\n|affiliations   = [[Association of Canadian Community Colleges|ACCC]], [[Canadian Colleges Athletic Association|CCAA]], [[Canadian Bureau for International Education|CBIE]]\n|website= [http://www.collegelasalle.com/ www.collegelasalle.com/]\n|}}\n \nFounded in 1959 in the LaSalle borough of [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], '''LaSalle College''' offers professional, college and pre-university training. It is the largest bilingual college in North America. LaSalle College offers over 60 programs (DEC, AEC and DEP).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lasallecollege.com/|title=LaSalle College Homepage|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> LaSalle College is composed of 6 schools: Fashion, Arts & Design, Hotel Management & Tourism, Business & Technologies, Social Sciences & Education, VFX & Game Design and E-learning.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lasallecollege.com/|title=LaSalle College Homepage|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nInternational students represent close to 40% of LaSalle College\u2019s student population.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lcieducation.com/|title=LCI Education Homepage|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=LCI Bogot\u00e1's new campus opens this December in the presence of the Governor General of Canada|url=http://www.newswire.ca/en/story/1458481/lci-bogota-s-new-campus-opens-this-december-in-the-presence-of-the-governor-general-of-canada|agency=CNW a PR Newswire Company}}</ref>\n\nLaSalle College graduates include Denis Gagnon,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://denisgagnon.ca/en/about/|title=About Denis Gagnon|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> Marie Saint-Pierre,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://districtmode.ca/en/details/designers/87/marie-saint-pierre|title=Designer - Marie Saint-Pierre|website=DistrictMode.com|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> Travis, Taddeo,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cafawards.ca/nominees/Travis-Taddeo.php|title=Designer - CAF Awards Nominees - Travis Taddeo|website=cafawards.ca|accessdate=19 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219184837/http://www.cafawards.ca/nominees/Travis-Taddeo.php|archive-date=19 December 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Anastasia Radevich,<ref>{{cite web|title=Sci-Fi Stompers|url=http://www.shoppingmtl.ca/blog/our-favourites/sci-fi-stompers/|website=shoppingmtl.ca|publisher=ShoppingMTL|accessdate=29 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141230212450/http://www.shoppingmtl.ca/blog/our-favourites/sci-fi-stompers/|archive-date=30 December 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Mariouche Gagn\u00e9,<ref>{{cite web|title=About - Harricana|url=http://www.harricana.qc.ca/corporate/en/about.html|website=www.harricana.qc.ca|publisher=Harricana|accessdate=29 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205012744/http://www.harricana.qc.ca/corporate/en/about.html|archive-date=5 February 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Annie Horth,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dumas|first1=Hugo|title=Annie et ses robes|url=http://www.lapresse.ca/debats/chroniques/hugo-dumas/201211/08/01-4591596-annie-et-ses-robes.php|accessdate=30 December 2014|work=La Presse}}</ref> Thomas Tait,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Friede|first1=EVa|title=LaSalle College Graduate wins top fashion prize|url=https://montrealgazette.com/life/fashion-beauty/lasalle-college-graduate-wins-top-fashion-prize|accessdate=19 December 2014|work=Montreal Gazette|date=May 28, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Blaid|first1=Sylvain|title=Designer New Wave// Thomas Tait|url=http://dresstokillmagazine.com/designer-new-wave-thomas-tait/|website=dresstokillmagazine.com|publisher=Dress To Kill Magazine|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> Gianni Falzone and Mike Derderian.<ref>{{cite web|title=People of Style - Pavoni|url=http://www.dolcemag.com/general-interest/people-of-style/pavoni/11894|website=dolcemag.com|publisher=Dolce Magazine|accessdate=29 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian nominee: Pavoni for Grammys|url=http://thechronicleherald.ca/artslife/643917-canadian-nominee-pavoni-for-grammys|website=thechronicleherald.ca|publisher=The Chronicle Herald|accessdate=29 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Fashionista.com ranked LaSalle College amongst\u2019 the world top 50 fashion schools.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sherman|first1=Lauren|title=Top 50 Fashion Schools in the World 2013: The Full List|url=http://fashionista.com/2013/06/top-50-fashion-schools-full-list|website=fashionista.com|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref>  In 2014, LaSalle College earned 4 prizes out of 5 at the Telio Design Competition.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Santerre|first1=Eric|title=Des fr\u00e8res jumeaux remportent le concoursT\u00e9lio|url=http://clindoeil.ca/mode/cest-hot/des-freres-jumeaux-remportent-le-concours-telio|website=clindoeil.ca|publisher=Clin d'Oeil|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Comp\u00e9tition T\u00e9lio|url=http://www.telio.com/archive/competition2014FR.html|website=telio.com|publisher=T\u00e9lio|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\nLaSalle College was founded in 1959 by Jean-Paul Morin, often referred to as \u00abthe father of fashion in Quebec\u00bb.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pierre|first1=Vall\u00e9e|title=Un r\u00e9seau de 21 \u00e9coles hors-Qu\u00e9bec - Le Coll\u00e8ge LaSalle s'affiche \u00e0 l'international|url=https://www.ledevoir.com/societe/education/226574/un-reseau-de-21-ecoles-hors-quebec-le-college-lasalle-s-affiche-a-l-international|accessdate=19 December 2014|work=Le Devoir|date=January 10, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Morin|first1=Jean-Paul|last2=Arbour|first2=Louise|title=Jean-Paul Morin, le fondateur du Coll\u00e8ge LaSalle et le p\u00e8re de la mode au Qu\u00e9bec|date=1999|publisher=Les \u00c9ditions Qu\u00e9becor|location=Montr\u00e9al|page=1}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Drolet-Giroux|first1=Mae|title=Jean-Paul Morin (1920-2012): la mode qu\u00e9b\u00e9coise en deuil de son p\u00e8re|url=http://www.lapresse.ca/actualites/passages/201209/03/01-4570599-jean-paul-morin-1920-2012-la-mode-quebecoise-en-deuil-de-son-pere.php|accessdate=19 December 2014|work=La Presse|date=September 3, 2012}}</ref> His goal was to give the Quebec population at the time new career opportunities by receiving education directly from experts.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}} The first program offered was a secretarial course.\n\n==Timeline==\n\n*1959:\tFounder, Jean-Paul Morin opens LaSalle Commercial College in Ville LaSalle and offers secretarial training.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Drolet-Giroux|first1=Mae|title=Jean-Paul Morin (1920-2012): la mode qu\u00e9b\u00e9coise en deuil de son p\u00e8re|url=http://www.lapresse.ca/actualites/passages/201209/03/01-4570599-jean-paul-morin-1920-2012-la-mode-quebecoise-en-deuil-de-son-pere.php|accessdate=19 December 2014|work=La Presse}}</ref>\n*1963:\tJean-Paul Morin sets a trend by taking initiative: his college is the first to hold an \"open house\", to print a color ad in Quebec and do television advertising.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Filion|first1=Louis Jacques|title=Savoir entreprendre \u2013 Douze mod\u00e8les de r\u00e9ussite \u2013 \u00c9tudes de cas, Montreal|date=2002|publisher=Les Presses de l\u2019Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|location=Montreal|page=54|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4Z53gG3mmdMC&pg=PA47|accessdate=19 December 2014|isbn=9782760618527}}</ref>\n*1966:\tDesigned by professors of the Fashion Institute of Technology of New York, LaSalle College launches its Fashion Marketing program.\nIn collaboration with Delta Airlines, LaSalle College launches its Airline Services program.\n*1970:\tA placement service is put in place for graduates of LaSalle College.\n*1971:\tIn collaboration with the Hotel Sheraton, LaSalle College launches its Hotel Management program.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Filion|first1=Louis-Jacques|title=Savoir entreprendre \u2013 Douze mod\u00e8les de r\u00e9ussite \u2013 \u00c9tudes de cas, Montreal, Les Presses de l'Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|date=2002|publisher=Les Presses de l\u2019Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|page=51|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4Z53gG3mmdMC&pg=PA47|isbn=9782760618527}}</ref>\n*1973:\tLaSalle College receives the status of \"collegial establishment\" from the minist\u00e8re de l\u2019\u00c9ducation du Qu\u00e9bec.\n\tL\u2019Ecole de mode du LaSalle College is born.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Filion|first1=Louis-Jacques|title=Savoir entreprendre \u2013 Douze mod\u00e8les de r\u00e9ussite \u2013 \u00c9tudes de cas, Montreal, Les Presses de l'Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|date=2002|publisher=Les Presses de l\u2019Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|page=47|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4Z53gG3mmdMC&pg=PA47&lpg=PA47|isbn=9782760618527}}</ref> The three-year Fashion Design program is launched whereby graduates receive a diploma of collegial studies (DEC)<ref>{{cite book|last1=Filion|first1=Louis-Jacques|title=Savoir entreprendre \u2013 Douze mod\u00e8les de r\u00e9ussite \u2013 \u00c9tudes de cas, Montreal, Les Presses de l'Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|date=2002|publisher=Les Presses de l\u2019Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|page=50|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4Z53gG3mmdMC&pg=PA47|isbn=9782760618527}}</ref>\n*1978: \tThe minist\u00e8re de l\u2019 \u00c9ducation du Qu\u00e9bec recognizes LaSalle College as the \"Centre specialis\u00e9 de la mode\"<ref>{{cite book|last1=Filion|first1=Louis-Jacques|title=Savoir entreprendre \u2013 Douze mod\u00e8les de r\u00e9ussite \u2013 \u00c9tudes de cas, Montreal, Les Presses de l'Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|date=2002|publisher=Les Presses de l\u2019Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|page=50|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4Z53gG3mmdMC&pg=PA47|isbn=9782760618527}}</ref>\n*1979: Mr. Jacques Marchand joins LaSalle College.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lacoursi\u00e8re|first1=Marie|title=Le Coll\u00e8ge LaSalle: exporter l'\u00e9ducation canadienne de Montr\u00e9al \u00e0 Casablanca|url=http://www.lescegeps.com/contributions_institutionnelles/contributions_internationales/internationalisation_de_la_formation/le_college_lasalle_exporter_leducation_canadienne_de_montreal_a_casablanca|website=lescegeps.com|publisher=LesCegeps.com|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> \n*1983:\t[[College Inter-Dec]] opens, offering programs in aesthetics and computer science.<ref>{{cite web|title=Inter-Dec College - About Us - History|url=http://www.interdeccollege.com/about-us/history.aspx|website=interdeccollege.com|publisher=Inter-Dec College|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref>\n*1988:\tJean-Paul Morin retires.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Filion|first1=Louis-Jacques|title=Savoir entreprendre \u2013 Douze mod\u00e8les de r\u00e9ussite \u2013 \u00c9tudes de cas, Montreal, Les Presses de l'Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|date=2002|publisher=Les Presses de l\u2019Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|page=78|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4Z53gG3mmdMC&pg=PA47|isbn=9782760618527}}</ref>\n*1988: Mrs Jacques Marchand and Jacques Lefebvre acquire the College.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Filion|first1=Louis-Jacques|title=Savoir entreprendre \u2013 Douze mod\u00e8les de r\u00e9ussite \u2013 \u00c9tudes de cas, Montreal, Les Presses de l'Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|date=2002|publisher=Les Presses de l\u2019Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al \u2013 Presses HEC|page=58|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4Z53gG3mmdMC&pg=PA47|isbn=9782760618527}}</ref>\n*1989:\tThe first LaSalle College International opens in Casablanca, Morocco.<ref>{{cite web|title==Portail du r\u00e9seau coll\u00e9gial - Internationalisation de la formation\n|last1=Lacoursi\u00e8re|first1=Marie|url=http://www.lescegeps.com/contributions_institutionnelles/contributions_internationales/internationalisation_de_la_formation/le_college_lasalle_exporter_leducation_canadienne_de_montreal_a_casablanca|website=lescegeps.com|publisher=Portail du R\u00e9seau Coll\u00e9gial du QU\u00e9bec|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref>\n*1989: The Fondation de la Mode de Montr\u00e9al is created to support training and research in the fashion industry.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fondation de la Mode de Montr\u00e9al - Fondation|url=http://www.fondationdelamodedemontreal.ca/la-fondation/|website=fondationdelamodedemontreal.ca|publisher=Fondation de la Mode de Montr\u00e9al}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Drolet-Giroux|first1=Mae|title=Jean-Paul Morin (1920-2012): la mode qu\u00e9b\u00e9coise en deuil de son p\u00e8re|url=http://www.lapresse.ca/actualites/passages/201209/03/01-4570599-jean-paul-morin-1920-2012-la-mode-quebecoise-en-deuil-de-son-pere.php|accessdate=19 December 2014|work=La Presse|publisher=La Presse|date=September 3, 2012}}</ref>\n*1995:\tl\u2019\u00c9cole sup\u00e9rieure de mode de Montr\u00e9al (\u00c9SMM) is created in partnership with l\u2019Universit\u00e9 de Qu\u00e9bec \u00e0 Montr\u00e9al offering a bachelor's degree in fashion design and management\n*1996:\tThe resto-bar Le Fuchsia opens and acts as a laboratory for the International School of Hotel Management and Tourism.<ref>{{cite web|title=Historique - Enseigner les r\u00e9alit\u00e9s de l'industrie|url=http://www.collegelasalle.com/a-propos/historique.aspx|website=collegelasalle.com|accessdate=22 December 2014}}</ref>\n*1996:\tThe Montr\u00e9al International Language Centre (MILC) is created providing courses in English and French as a second language as long with seven other foreign languages \n*1998:\tLaSalle College International opens in Vancouver, BC.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sam|first1=Miranda|title=LaSalle College Launches New Campus and Brand|url=http://www.stylebyfire.ca/2014/11/28/lasalle-college-new-campus/|website=stylebyfire.ca|publisher=Style By Fire}}</ref>\n*2000:\t LaSalle College opens an e-learning school and invests in developing online learning solutions.{{buzzword inline|date=August 2019}}\n*2010:\tUXIBUS is launched, a website for graduates to showcase their work, search for jobs and where employers can browse through profiles to find potential candidates.<ref>{{cite web|title=Uxibus - Ressources|url=http://www.uxibus.com/Ressources.aspx|website=uxibus.com|publisher=LCI Education}}</ref>\n*2014:\tAfter 25 years, LaSalle College changes its image and logo.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Daguzan Bernier|first1=Myriam|title=Coll\u00e8ge LaSalle : Nouvelle image, nouvelles avenues|url=http://journalmetro.com/plus/carrieres/446314/college-lasalle-nouvelle-image-nouvelles-avenues/|accessdate=19 December 2014|work=M\u00e9tro|publisher=TC M\u00e9dia|date=February 11, 2014}}</ref>\n*2014:\tClaude Marchand becomes CEO of LCI Education.\n*2015: Melbourne's [[Academy of Design Australia]] joins the LCI network, alongside a new state of the art campus in [[Collingwood, Victoria]].\n*2017: LCI Education network acquires [[The Art Institute of Vancouver]] which continues as LaSalle College Vancouver, in [[Vancouver, Canada]].\n\n==Schools==\n\nLaSalle College has six schools under its banner, each specializing in their respective industries:\n\n*International School of Fashion, Arts and Design\n*International School of Hotel Management and Tourism\n*School of Social Sciences and Education\n*International School of Business and Technologies\n*School of VFX & Game Design\n*School of E-learning\n\n==Programs==\nThe College is part of the Quebec educational system and grants 3 types of diplomas:\n\n*Pre-university and technical programs&nbsp;\u2013 DEC: A diploma of college studies (DEC) can either give a student access to university or the job market.\n*Continuing education and technical programs&nbsp;\u2013 AEC:  An attestation of college studies (AEC) serves to reorient one\u2019s career or quickly acquire a skill set applicable in the job market.\n*Vocational training&nbsp;\u2013 DVS: A diploma of vocational studies (DVS or DEP in French) is a diploma that prepares students for direct employment.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of colleges in Quebec]]\n* [[Higher education in Quebec]]\n* [[Canadian Interuniversity Sport]]\n* [[Canadian government scientific research organizations]]\n* [[Canadian university scientific research organizations]]\n* [[Canadian industrial research and development organizations]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Qc Uni|CEGEP=yes}}\n{{Commons}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Vocational education in Canada]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Montreal]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1959]]\n[[Category:1959 establishments in Quebec]]\n[[Category:Private universities and colleges in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|text=[[La Salle College]], Hong Kong}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2007}}\n{{advert|date=March 2013}}\n}}\n{{Infobox University\n|name         = LaSalle College/Mo